{"type": "root", "attrs": {"type": "node", "context": "vop", "internal": "volumesample", "icon": "VOP/volumesample", "version": null, "namespace": null}, "body": [{"level": 0, "type": "title", "indent": 0, "text": ["Volume Sample"], "extent": [75, 93]}, {"type": "summary", "indent": 0, "text": ["Samples the value of a volume primitive."], "extent": [93, 142]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["Samples a specific volume primitive. Returns 0 if ", {"type": "code", "text": ["primnum"]}, " or\n", {"type": "code", "text": ["input_index"]}, " is out of range, or the given primitive is not a volume\nprimitive."], "extent": [142, 287]}, {"type": "note_group", "body": [{"type": "note", "indent": 0, "role": "item", "extent": [287, 293], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["This node is only available in the geometry context."], "extent": [293, 351]}], "container": true}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["Using ", {"type": "code", "text": ["volumesample()"]}, " functions on points outside of a volume box will extend the sign distance field if the volume boundary is SDF. The distance to the bounding box is added to the streaked bounding box value."], "extent": [351, 564]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["The following diagram shows how the SDF extension works."], "extent": [564, 622]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": [{"scheme": "Image", "value": "/images/volumesample.jpg", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/images/volumesample.jpg"}], "extent": [622, 656]}, {"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Boundary values"], "extent": [656, 678], "body": [{"type": "bullet_group", "body": [{"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": ["Constant values mean there is a value that all outside samples are set to (usually 0). So even if the border voxel is 1, as soon as you peak outside it is 0."], "extent": [678, 840]}, {"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": ["Streak means the boundary value is held into the surrounding area. So an out-of-bound sample is clamped to the volume and the value samples. This means a value of 1 at the boundary will streak into the surrounding space."], "extent": [840, 1064]}, {"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": ["Repeat means space is tiled with the volume."], "extent": [1064, 1112]}], "container": true}]}, {"level": 1, "id": "related", "container": true, "type": "related_section", "indent": 0, "role": "section", "extent": [1112, 1121], "body": [{"type": "bullet_group", "body": [{"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": [{"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/vop/volumesamplefile", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/volumesamplefile"}], "extent": [1121, 1155]}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": [{"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/vop/volumegradient", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/volumegradient"}], "extent": [1155, 1187]}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": [{"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/vop/volumegradientfile", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/volumegradientfile"}], "extent": [1187, 1224]}], "container": true}], "text": "Related"}], "title": ["Volume Sample"], "summary": ["Samples the value of a volume primitive."]}